Subject: Kerbal Space Program
Description: Kerbal Space Program (KSP) has taken computer gaming and brought it crashing into the realm of a true space simulator. In KSP, you build rockets, launch them, get them into space, do SCIENCE! there, build space stations and moon bases... do SCIENCE! there, and travel to other worlds... and do more SCIENCE!  Kerbal Space Program is like being a kid in a candy store the size of the solar system!  Speakers include:Bob Trembley - Track: Science, Gaming  - Duration: 50 minutes

Subject: Solar Observing
Description: ReRoot Pontiac, a newly founded non-profit located in Pontiac, MI would like to share its mission. We are a group of students, scientists,  gardeners and entrepreneurs focused on developing interest in science, technology, engineering and mathematics. To achieve this we are designing and building interactive spaces containing examples of sustainable energies and natural systems to promote experiential learning.  Speakers include:Bob Trembley - Track: Science  - Duration: 50 minutes

Subject: AsteroidDay
Description: Bob Trembly and Krunal Desai talk all things asteroids, and what we need to know about them.   Speakers include:Bob Trembley, Krunal Desai - Track: Science  - Duration: 50 minutes

Subject: Night Sky Observing
Description: Join Bob Trembley to observe what the late spring night sky has to offer!  Speakers include:Bob Trembley - Track: Science  - Duration: 1 hour and 50 minutes

Subject: Kerbal Space Build-Off
Description: Build you own rocket - see if you can get it into orbit! Play with Kerbal Space Program yourself, and learn about its amazing potential as both a game and educational space simulator.  Speakers include:Bob Trembley, Daniel Dugan - Track: Tech  - Duration: 1 hour and 50 minutes
